<HEAD>Slots Banned In Laundries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Slot machines line the walls of supermarkets and bars in this gaming resort, but they do n't belong in doughnut shops or laundries, officials decided. <ORGANIZATION> Clark </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commissioners </ORGANIZATION> voted Monday to prohibit new slot machine licenses for machines in laundries, bakeries, doughnut shops, fast-food restaurants, movie theaters and professional offices. Existing licenses are not affected. Several owners of self-service laundries said they depend on slot machine revenue to cover the high cost of doing business, with the slots generating about 25 percent of revenues. Other laundry owners stressed that customers need something to do to keep occupied while their clothes spin and tumble. Commissioners said it is too hard to regulate the machines if they are allowed to continue to proliferate in different businesses.
</TEXT>
