<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Winter Olympics on television and a drop in the number of new movies contributed to a sluggish weekend at the box office. `` Good Morning, Vietnam'' was the No. 1 film for the seventh week. `` The openings were n't strong and the Olympics did very well in the ratings, particularly on Sunday. The box office was hurt on Sunday,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Krier </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which compiles the weekly turnstile figures. `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>,'' which got <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> an Oscar nomination for his portrayal of a raucous <LOCATION> Saigon </LOCATION> disc jockey, earned $ 5.2 million for a nine-week total of $ 78.5 million. In second place was <PERSON> Roman </PERSON> <PERSON> Polanski </PERSON>'s `` Frantic'' with $ 4.35 million in ticket sales. It was another good week for <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Studios </ORGANIZATION>, with three movies remaining in the Top 5. In addition to `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>,'' Disney-Touchstone films has the <PERSON> Sidney </PERSON> <PERSON> Poitier </PERSON> movie `` Shoot to Kill'' in third with a $ 3.5 million take and `` Three Men and a Baby,'' fifth in its 13th week of release. The offbeat romantic film `` Moonstruck'' was fourth with $ 3.3 million. The only other new entry in the Top 10 was `` Night in the Life of <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON>,'' a teen movie starring <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>. It earned $ 2.7 million in its first week, to place sixth. `` Action Jackson'' was seventh with $ 2.4 million, `` Broadcast News'' was eighth with $ 1.349 million, `` She's Having a Baby'' was ninth with $ 1.340 million and the creepy `` The Serpent and the Rainbow'' was 10th with $ 1.32 million. Studios use the weekend box office to determine how well a movie is doing. Here are the top films for the weekend as tallied by <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross, number of weeks in release and estimated production costs. Films where costs are not available are maked n-a. 1. `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 5.23 million, 1,598 screens, $ 3,275 per screen, $ 78.49 million, nine weeks, $ 21 million. 2. `` Frantic,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 4.35 million, 1,101 screens, $ 3,960 per screen, $ 4.35 million, one week, n-a. 3. `` Shoot to Kill,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 3.51 million, 1,482 screens, $ 2,371 per screen, $ 16.92 million, three weeks, n-a. 4. `` Moonstruck,'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>, $ 3.37 million, 1,178 screens, $ 2,867 per screen, $ 41.2 million, 10 weeks, $ 17 million. 5. `` Three Men And A Baby,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 2.86 million, 1,615 screens, $ 1,773 per screen, $ 140.34 million, 13 weeks, $ 18 million. 6. `` Night in the Life of <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON>,'' 20th Century-Fox, $ 2.73 million, 881 screens, $ 3,107 per screen, $ 2.73 million, one week, n-a. 7. `` Action <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Lorimar </PERSON>, $ 2.43 million, 1,243 screens, $ 1,956 per screen, $ 13.51 million, three weeks, n-a. 8. `` Broadcast News,'' 20th Century-Fox, $ 1.35 million, 826 screens, $ 1,634 per screen, $ 42.52 million, 10 weeks, $ 15 million. 9. `` She's Having a Baby,'' Paramount, $ 1.34 million, 1,009 screens, $ 1,328 per screen, $ 12.44 million, three weeks, n-a. 10. `` The Serpent and the Rainbow,'' Universal, $ 1.32 million, 874 screens, $ 1,520 per screen, $ 16.52 million, three weeks, $ 8 million.
