none were left, <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said. `` That means that at least 25 citizens might have a -LRB- live bomb -RRB- in their house or on their property,'' <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said. Investigators suspect it was a cache of Confederate munitions, he said. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said the bomb squad would pick up any suspect cannonballs for free and return them if they can be defused without damage. <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION> officials plan to notify state and county authorities in <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> about the discovery, <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said.
