<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A site-selection task force this week recommended that the Board of Pensions of the Presbyterian Church -LRB- USA -RRB- be based in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>. The choice, subject to ratification by the church's general assembly in June, was among these three potential sites: <LOCATION> Louisville </LOCATION>, where the newly merged denomination has established its headquarters; <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, where the former Southern branch had its headquarters, or <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> where the Northern branch had its pension board.
