<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A leader of the fundamentalist wing of <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Baptists </ORGANIZATION> predicts that that its candidate for president will be the Rev. <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Vines </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, opposing the Rev. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ariz </LOCATION>. Both take a conservative view of Scripture, the Rev. <PERSON> Paige </PERSON> <PERSON> Patterson </PERSON>, a fundamentalist leader, said in predicting their candidacies, but he said <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> has been co-opted by the moderates. To maintain the nine-year resurgence of conservative-fundamentalists at the denomination's convention in June, he said, they must back `` an inerrantist for president who will do their bidding.'' `` Inerrantists'' maintain Scripture is without factual error.
