<HEAD>Dr Pepper, Seven-Up In Tentative Agreement To Combine Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Blending the operations of Dr <ORGANIZATION> Pepper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and The <ORGANIZATION> Seven-Up </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> will allow the companies to continue an aggressive style in the beverage industry, company officials say. The boards of directors at holding companies for Dr Pepper and <ORGANIZATION> Seven-Up </ORGANIZATION> announced the merger of operations on Monday. The transaction, which is contingent on a definitive agreement and regulatory approval, was expected to be completed in 60 to 90 days. Groups led by the Dallas-based investment partnership <ORGANIZATION> Hicks </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> acquired Dr Pepper and Seven-Up October in separate transactions during 1986. One group acquired <ORGANIZATION> Dr </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pepper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> for $ 416 million in August 1986 and another group bought <ORGANIZATION> Seven </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Up </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> for $ 240 million two months later. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hicks </PERSON> and <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Haas </PERSON>, co-chairmen of both companies, said the merger was a culmination of `` superb achievement'' at both companies since their acquisition. No management changes were expected, the pair said in a prepared statement `` The combination of our two companies will enable us to continue our aggressive style in this industry, as demonstrated by our recent introduction of two new products, 7Up Gold and Diet 7Up Gold,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Albers </PERSON>, who is chief executive of both companies. The operations of the two companies have been increasingly integrated in recent months, the companies said. For instance, they each have used manufacturing facilities in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> to produce soft drink concentrate. `` The merger will allow the companies to be completely operated as one company, which has obvious advantages internally and in the marketplace,'' said <PERSON> Albers </PERSON>. The trade newsletter Beverage Digest estimated the two companies captured about 10.7 percent of the $ 38 billion soft drink market in 1987, up from 10.4 percent the previous year. The soft drink leaders are <ORGANIZATION> Coca-Cola </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, whose various brands accounted for 40.3 percent of the soft drink market last year, and <ORGANIZATION> Pepsi-Cola </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which had 30.2 percent, according to the newsletter based in <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Conn. </LOCATION> `` This formalizes a close and efficient relationship,'' said <PERSON> Emanuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, who follows the beverage industry for the investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Montgomery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>. `` It will help them compete better in the marketplace.'' Upon completion of the merger, significant owners of the combined enterprise will include senior management; <ORGANIZATION> Hicks </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Haas </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Cadbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Schweppes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Donaldson </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lufkin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Jenrette </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Citicorp </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Venture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION>.
