 <ORGANIZATION> Affiliated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Publications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, owner of the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Globe </ORGANIZATION>, said Tuesday it has bought a 40 percent equity interest in <ORGANIZATION> Xyquest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Billerica </LOCATION>, a developer of software for word processing and publishing systems. Under the agreement, Affiliated will pay $ 3 million for newly issued <ORGANIZATION> Xyquest </ORGANIZATION> shares. <ORGANIZATION> Xyquest </ORGANIZATION>, founded six years ago, developed the XyWrite word processing line. In prepared remarks, Affiliated President <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Giuggio </PERSON> said of the investment, `` This is an exciting young company with a promising future in electronic publishing. <ORGANIZATION> Xyquest </ORGANIZATION> has an excellent management team, and we're delighted to be associated with it.'' <ORGANIZATION> Xyquest </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hild </PERSON> said the company's long-term goals for product development include creating a full range of tools for writing and editing and continuing to expand into corporate word processing. Affiliated is parent company of <ORGANIZATION> Globe </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Newspaper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which publishes the Globe. It also owns <ORGANIZATION> Billboard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Publications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, The <ORGANIZATION> Globe </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pequot </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, and a major interest in <ORGANIZATION> McCaw </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cellular </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>.
